title: Netflix Debuts First Trailer for Aziz Ansari's 'Master of None'
text:
Comments Meet Dev, an actor who has trouble deciding what he wants to eat, much less the pathway for the rest of his life. 
The first trailer for Aziz Ansari 's new show " Master of None " has arrived for viewing pleasure, introducing the viewers to Dev, his family, and friends. The promo video offers a sneak peek at some hilarious scenes including an awkward bedroom scene. Dev is a 30-year-old actor in New York. He has trouble deciding what he wants to eat, much less the pathway for the rest of his life. The story takes him through subjects as diverse as the plight of the elderly, the immigrant experience, and how to find the most delicious pasta for dinner. The new comedy show is set to premiere on the streaming service on November 6. It is supported by Noel Wells, Eric Wareheim, Lena Waithe, Kelvin Yu, and H. Jon Benjamin.
